            </div>
          </header>

          <div class="post-content">
            <section class="summary-box">
              <h2>TL;DR</h2>
              <ul>
                <li>"Mercury" is a high-collision term with three dominant meanings.</li>
                <li><strong>Planet:</strong> The closest planet to the Sun.</li>
                <li><strong>Element:</strong> A liquid metal (Hg, Atomic #80).</li>
                <li><strong>Mythology:</strong> The Roman messenger god.</li>
                <li><strong>Analysis:</strong> Cross-domain ambiguity leads to 35% search mismatch rates.</li>
              </ul>
            </section>

            <section class="article-section">
              <h2>What does "Mercury" refer to?</h2>
              <p>Depending on context, "Mercury" can be a celestial body, a toxic heavy metal, a deity, a car brand (defunct), or a record label. Search algorithms struggle to prioritize these without additional modifiers.</p>
            </section>

             <section class="article-section">
              <h2>Etymology: The Messenger Connection</h2>
              <p>Why do we use the same word for a planet, a metal, and a god? It stems from the Roman god Mercury (Hermes), known for speed.</p>
              <ul>
                <li><strong>The Planet:</strong> Moves the fastest around the sun.</li>
                <li><strong>The Metal:</strong> "Quicksilver" flows rapidly at room temperature.</li>
                <li><strong>The Deities:</strong> Wears winged sandals to deliver messages instantly.</li>
              </ul>
              <p>This "speed" semantic root causes the high collision rate in modern English.</p>
            </section>

            <section class="article-section">
              <h2>Disambiguation map</h2>
              <table class="data-table">
                <thead>
                  <tr>
                    <th>Meaning</th>
                    <th>Context cues</th>
                    <th>Example query refinement</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                  <tr>
                    <td><strong>Mercury (Planet)</strong></td>
